  m_text: 'AR-med  Privacy Policy

    Last updated: March 2026



    1. Information
    We Collect

    AR-med collects only the minimum information necessary to provide
    the application''s features. When you register an account, we collect your email
    address and a securely hashed password through Firebase Authentication. We do
    not collect your name, phone number, location, or any other personal identifiers.



    2.
    How We Use Your Information

    Your email and password are used solely to authenticate
    your identity and grant you access to the application. We do not use your information
    for marketing, advertising, or any purpose other than account access.



    3.
    Data Storage

    Your credentials are stored securely on Firebase servers managed
    by Google. AR-med does not operate its own backend server. All 3D anatomical
    models, quiz content, and AR features are embedded directly in the application
    and do not transmit any data to external servers during use.



    4. Camera
    Access

    AR-med requires access to your device camera to enable Vuforia image
    target tracking. The camera feed is processed entirely on your device in real
    time and is never recorded, stored, or transmitted.



    5. Data Sharing

    We
    do not sell, share, or disclose your personal information to any third party.
    Your data is not used for analytics, advertising networks, or any commercial
    purpose.



    6. Your Rights

    You may request deletion of your account
    and associated data at any time by contacting us. Upon deletion, your email and
    credentials will be permanently removed from Firebase.



    7. Children

    AR-med
    is intended for use by medical and health science students. We do not knowingly
    collect data from children under the age of 13.



    8. Changes to This Policy

    We
    may update this Privacy Policy as the application develops. Any changes will
    be reflected with an updated date at the top of this document.



    9. Contact

    For
    any privacy-related questions, contact: c.akunyiba@alustudent.com




    AR-med
    End User License Agreement

    Last updated: March 2026



    Please read this
    agreement carefully before using AR-med. By installing or using this application,
    you agree to be bound by the terms below.



    1. License Grant

    African
    Leadership University and the developer, Akunyiba Chimdalu Divinefavour, grant
    you a limited, non-exclusive, non-transferable, revocable license to install
    and use AR-med on your personal Android device solely for educational and non-commercial
    purposes.



    2. Restrictions

    You may not copy, modify, distribute, sell,
    or reverse engineer any part of this application. You may not use AR-med for
    commercial purposes or represent it as your own work. You may not attempt to
    extract, reuse, or redistribute the 3D anatomical models, scripts, or any other
    assets contained within the application.



    3. Educational Use Only

    AR-med
    is designed as a supplementary educational tool for anatomy learning. It is not
    a medical device and must not be used for clinical diagnosis, medical decision-making,
    or patient care. All anatomical content is provided for learning purposes only.



    4.
    Account Responsibility

    You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality
    of your login credentials. You agree not to share your account with others or
    create accounts on behalf of other individuals.



    5. Intellectual Property

    All
    content within AR-med, including 3D models, scripts, UI designs, and educational
    content, is the intellectual property of the developer unless otherwise stated.
    All rights not expressly granted are reserved.



    6. Disclaimer of Warranties

    AR-med
    is provided as is without warranty of any kind. The developer does not guarantee
    uninterrupted or error-free operation of the application. Use of the application
    is at your own risk.



    7. Limitation of Liability

    To the maximum extent
    permitted by law, the developer shall not be liable for any damages arising from
    your use of or inability to use AR-med, including but not limited to data loss,
    device damage, or any medical decisions made based on content viewed in the application.



    8.
    Termination

    This license is effective until terminated. It will terminate
    automatically if you violate any of its terms. Upon termination you must delete
    all copies of the application from your devices.



    9. Governing Law

    This
    agreement is governed by the laws of Rwanda. Any disputes arising from this agreement
    shall be resolved in accordance with Rwandan law.



    10. Contact

    For
    any questions regarding this agreement, contact: c.akunyiba@alustudent.com'
